  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>- Overall responsible for surveying of construction sites for all aspects of Boundary, GPS, Topographic, Control Surveying, land titles etc. for Civil/LTA and MRT projects</p><p>- Supervise the survey and coordinate with the construction and design team using approved pre-computation plans to meet clients' specifications</p><p>- Responsible for the coordination of the whole project as per site progress schedule, liaise with client/authorities on technical issues</p><p>- Ensure shop drawings are produced and approved on time with accuracy</p><p>- To plan and closely manage the surveying work schedule</p><p>- Uses trigonometry and other mathematic functions extensively</p><p>- Responsible for providing accurate survey data</p><p>- Creates proper drawings on completed survey points installed on site</p><p>- Ad-hoc duties as assigned by superior(s)</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>- Degree or Diploma in land surveying, Geology or Civil Engineering, recognized by LSB</p><p>- Minimum 8 years of relevant experience as Registered Surveyor for Civil/ LTA and MRT projects in Singapore</p><p>- A registered Surveyor under Land Surveyors Act (issued with a certification of registration)</p><p>- Knowledge in CADD using AutoCAD, Civil3D BIM, Revit, MicroStation</p><p>- Familiar with and able to interpret structural, architectural and M&E drawings, for coordination work</p><p>- Geo Spatial Diploma</p>",
